# ETHICAL LICENSING DECLARATION

The Davenport CEMEX Master Plan repository utilizes a strictly divided, ethically reciprocal licensing structure to ensure the project remains a permanent, open-source municipal asset. 

By utilizing, modifying, or contributing to this repository, you legally agree to the following designated licenses:

1. HARDWARE & MECHANICAL BLUEPRINTS: CERN-OHL-S v2
All physical engineering designs, mechanical blueprints, silo retrofits, ceramic pipe routing, and solid-state infrastructure integrations are licensed under the CERN Open Hardware Licence - Strongly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-S v2). Any physical facility built or modified using these schematics must return its design improvements to the public domain. You may not patent these physical layouts.
Full License Text: https://ohwr.org/cernohl

2. CONTROL SOFTWARE & ALGORITHMS: GNU GPLv3
All software code governing the Just-In-Time (JIT) logistics, TEG energy harvesting calculations, automated centrifuges, and autonomous drone flight paths is licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPLv3). 
Full License Text: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html

3. CIVIC PROPOSALS & DOCUMENTATION: CC BY-SA 4.0
All text, Master Blogs, financial spreadsheets, Local Coastal Program (LCP) Amendment drafts, and infographics are licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0). You may share and adapt this material for civic use, provided you give appropriate credit to Paul Statchen and distribute your contributions under the same open-source license.
Full License Text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/
